    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "script: render BIP-388 wallet policies in getdescriptorinfo",
    "user": {
      "login": "rxbryan",
      "id": 33056740,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzMDU2NzQw",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33056740?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/rxbryan",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rxbryan/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Hardware signing devices use BIP-388 wallet policies to display spending conditions to users before signing. getdescriptorinfo has no way to return such a representation.\r\n\r\nThis PR extends getdescriptorinfo to return wallet_policy_template and `wallet_policy_keys` for BIP-388 policy-compatible multipath `<M;N>/*` descriptors. Adds `ParseDescriptorInfo()` to centralize descriptor analysis and make it reusable from the RPC, GUI, and external signer tooling, exposing `ParseDescriptorInfo`, `WalletPolicy`, and `DescriptorInfo` for downstream consumers.\r\n\r\nSupported: `pkh`, `wpkh`, `sh`, `wsh`, `tr`, `multi`, `sortedmulti`, `multi_a`, `sortedmulti_a`, with optional musig() in the tr keypath or script leaves. Tests cover the BIP-388 spec vectors plus negative cases for repeated keys, non-disjoint multipath expressions, and derivation-before-aggregation in `musig`.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n- [ ] Miniscript policy rendering\r\n- [ ] Expose `ParseDescriptorInfo` through interfaces::Node\r\n\r\ncloses #32659 ",
